 one. Has a bit of a unique visual style that some don't like, but I'd describe the experience as very gritty and brutal.<br>\
Kaiju No. 8 is a real spectacle, giant monsters getting annihilated in flashy ways.<br>\
Dr. Stone makes science cool. It's a fun ride, and while the early seasons are pretty solid, it REALLY picks up after season 2. The MC is very, very opposed to romance, so you won't have to worry too much about that. Any time it's brought up it's either as a gag or just glossed over and forgotten about.</p>\
<p>Unfortunately most of what I watch either has romance elements in it or literally is just a romance, so this is all I've got that's recent.<br>\
And <em>also</em> unfortunately you'll be missing out on the Fate series, which I adore. Lot of romance in that though, so I suppose it's disqualified.</p>\
